The article announces a historic breakthrough in the Middle East, with Israel and Lebanon agreeing to end their maritime boundary dispute and establish a permanent maritime boundary between them. The agreement was achieved after months of mediation by the United States, with the support of France. The focus is on using energy as a tool for cooperation, stability, security, and prosperity in the region. The agreement will allow for the development of energy fields, benefiting both countries and promoting a more stable and prosperous region. It also protects Israel's security and economic interests and provides Lebanon with the opportunity to exploit its own energy resources. The United States sees this agreement as promoting its interests in a more stable and integrated Middle East. The article emphasizes the efforts of diplomats and the bipartisan support for this issue.